            <p><italic>To illustrate the MeSH-based cluster annotations and similarities, let us consider two entities,</italic><monospace>supranuclear palsy, progressive, 3</monospace><italic>and</italic><monospace>secondary parkinson disease</monospace><italic>. The terms correspond to the MeSH tree code sets</italic> {<monospace>C10.228.662.700</monospace>, …, <monospace>C23.888.592.636.447.690</monospace>, …, <monospace>C11.590.472.500</monospace>, …} <italic>and</italic> {<monospace>C10.228.662.600.700</monospace>}<italic>, respectively, which are also the sets of specific clusters associated with the terms. The top-level clusters are</italic> {<monospace>C10</monospace>, <monospace>C11</monospace>, <monospace>C23</monospace>}<italic>and</italic> {<monospace>C10</monospace>}<italic>, respectively. The least common subsumer of the two terms is</italic>
